Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, drain the @sweetcorn{160%grams} in a #sieve{}.

Pour the @water for the couscous{240%milliliter(s)} and half the @chicken stock paste{10%grams} into a #saucepan{}. Bring to the boil.

Remove from the heat, stir in the @couscous{120%grams} and cover. Leave to the side, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken thigh{260%grams} and sweetcorn. Fry, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Next, stir in the @tomato puree{30%grams}, @chipotle paste{20%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), remaining @chicken stock paste{10%grams}, @water for the sauce{125%milliliter(s)} and @sugar for the sauce{½%tsp}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat. Simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from the heat. Stir in the @BBQ sauce{48%grams} and @butter{20%grams}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share the couscous and chicken stew between #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @crispy onions{1%sachet}.

Enjoy!